I'm sure they will incorporate a dictionary. But it's not a problem. Here is what I write for <a href="http://bbantispam.com/atc/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Advanced Textual Confirmation</a>:
<br />

<br />
To pass ATC, spammers will have to collect a database of question and answers. This work requires a human. Even if spammers pay as low as 1 cent per forum, 100,000 forums will cost them $1,000. And database maintenence is even more costly.
<br />

<br />
Therefore, for spammer it is much more profitable to skip the sites protected by ATC. They'll better spam unprotected one.<br />_________________<br />Oleg Parashchenko, bbAntiSpam
